experience.description:
2024-05 to 2024-09, Retail & E-commerce Company– Senior Frontend Engineer
- Frontend centered team of 6 engineers, focused on the product details page for one of the biggest retail companies of Canada
- Maintain and develop new features with a focus on scalability, responsiveness, and performance;
- Implement features to boost customer engagement and ultimately increase their loyalty and spending;
- Continued leading Accenture’s React Academy while updating outdated materials to include modern React concepts and best practices.

2023-11 to 2024-04, Consultancy Company – Senior Frontend Engineer
- Continue working on the previous project but with additional responsibilities;
- Lead a team of 5 Frontend Engineers, actively estimating the work in the backlog and defining the priorities for deliveries;
- Organize technical discussions to improve codebase and devops process;
- Provide technical support to the team members;
- Lead Accenture's React academy, successfully helping 10+ junior developers start their journey / improve their knowledge in JavaScript and React.

2023-01 to 2023-11, Consultancy Company – Frontend Engineer
– Maitain and improve a large React solution to improve processing of large datasets;
– Design and implement multiple new features, including an AI powered chat-bot that helped the user create the pipeline to process the datasets through text;
– Perform 2 demos to several potencial clients about some of the new features developed;
– Develop global components, very generic, that can be shared across the whole application;
– Improve redux store to manage data shared across the several areas of the application;
– Perform several code reviews to ensure the codebase stays clean and consistent, and follows all the project’s guidelines;
– Work with multiple services from AWS (CloudFront, S3, Lambda, API Gateway) and GCP (App Engine, Cloud Storage, Cloud Functions);

2022-02 to 2022-12, Energy Company – Frontend Engineer
– Work in close collaboration with the client to understand the application requirements;
– Develop multiple web applications, using Laravel for the backend and Angular for the frontend, following software development best practices;
– Develop multiple Angular global components, highly customizable, that helped reduce the development time;
– Work together with other client’s teams on these projects, maintaining good organization and communication;
– Improve and maintain an internal Angular component library shared across the multiple applications
– Integrate application with multiple Google Cloud services (i.e., storage buckets) using Google Cloud SDK.
Technologies: JavaScript, TypeScript, Angular, CSS5, Git

2021-07 to 2022-01, Lifesciences Company – Integration Engineer
Integration platform project with the goal of improving the lives of patients fighting cardiovascular disease by connecting client's solution, responsible for collecting and monitoring patient information, with multiple EMRs.
– Understand solution requirements in close collaboration with the client;
– Lead technical discussions with the client and provide help on technical and integration decisions;
– Design solution architecture based on Azure cloud services, using UML diagrams;
– Develop solution using Mirth (Java/Javascript) and integrate it with Azure services like Azure VMs and Microsoft Azure SQL;
– Integrate solution with Azure-based services developed by the other client’s teams;
– Perform unit, functional, and integration tests;
– Onboard and train 4 junior integration developers;

2021-01 to 2021-02, GCP Initiative – Integration Engineer
Integration platform project aiming to connect the client’s solution, a system that helps doctors to take better care of patients with hypertension, with multiple hospital sites using an event-driven approach.
– Work with the client on a daily basis;
– Provide support in technical discussions with the client;
– Develop solution based on Mirth (Java/Javascript), as the core to ingest, process, transform and transmit information, and integrate it with AWS services such as S3 Buckets and AWS Aurora;
– Document architecture of the solution’s integration engine component (Mirth);
– Perform unit, functional, integration and stress tests.
